profile_positions.description:
Bluebook trainee atvDG INTPA -- International Partnerships, F.4 Sustainable Transport, and Urban Development  
(former DG DEVCO -- Development Cooperation, C.5 Cities, Local Authorities, Digitalisation, Infrastructure (EuropeAid))

The main activities in DG INTPA included:
• Promoting the urban context as a driver for growth and sustainable development in EU Delegations through presentations, essays, and academic content;
• Supporting the so-called Team Europe Initiatives (TEIs) in Africa, Latin America, and the Caribbean. The TEIs package aims at supporting partner countries in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic and its consequences. Its objective is to combine resources from the EU, its Member States, and other financial institutions (European Investment Bank, European Bank for Reconstruction and Development). My role is to observe and analyse TEIs objectives and orient its approach through spatial and urban development;
•  Assisting in the preparation and establishment of urban indicators for financial aid (Capacity4dev);
•  Supported and participated in the creation of "Quick Tips" to integrate environmental and climate change into the urban development context (Green Deal);
• Participated in discussions related to the EU Budget for the Future namely NDICI and Programming tools for development.
